I in Australia, India and the United States – and the rather different cases of Ireland and New Zealand – the book concludes by looking at how the disruptive, dynamic and democratic effects of FOI laws continue to cause controversy once in operation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFreedom of informationxGreat Britain. 0aFreedom of informationzGreat Britain. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aLAW / Public.2bisacsh  aFOI.  aNew Labour.  aTony Blair.  ademocracy.  afreedom of information.  aopenness.  atransparency.1 aWorthy, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610851740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526108517423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526108517/original  a978-3-11-128281-7  Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles